FBIS3-23125 "jptot010__l94088" JPRS-TOT-94-010-L Document Type:JPRS Document Title:Terrorism FOUO 10 March 1994 NEAR EAST/SOUTH ASIA ISRAEL Update on, Reactions to Hebron Mosque Massacre Qiryat Arba' Not Obeying Closure TA2702092594 Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el in Hebrew 0800 GMT 27 Feb 94 TA2702092594 Jerusalem Qol Yisra'el Language: Hebrew Article Type:BFN [Excerpt] The territories are under full closure since this morning and their residents are banned from coming to work in Israel until further notice. Our correspondent Gil Litman reports that a closure was also clamped on Qiryat Arba'. In practice, however, it is not being observed and every two hours a convoy of cars and a bus to Jerusalem leave Hebron and Qiryat Arba'. The convoys are escorted by IDF [Israel Defense Forces] troops due to stone-throwing incidents in the area of Halhul. [passage omitted on rioting]
